        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 20 at 1:20PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ridgefield, or near St. Helens, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Battle Ground, Ridgefield, Venersborg, Dollar Corner, Meadow Glade,
Cherry Grove, Lewisville, Hockinson, Heisson, and Brush Prairie.

This includes the following highways in Washington...
Interstate 5 between mile markers 12 and 16.
State Route 503 between mile markers 7 and 14.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
